data.name: Orange Glazed Salmon
data.quickTastyDescription: A delightful salmon fillet glazed with a sweet and tangy orange sauce, perfect for any weeknight dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix together the orange juice, honey, soy sauce, minced garlic, and grated ginger to create the glaze.
Place the salmon fillets in a baking dish and pour the glaze over them.
Drizzle olive oil on top and season with salt and pepper.
Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes, or until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.
Garnish with chopped green onions before serving.
data.detailedName: Sweet and Tangy Orange Glazed Salmon
